Post.create!(
  title_hr: "Inside Out -- Sljeme",
  body_hr: <<-EOS.strip_heredoc,
    Nakon naše internacionalne uspješnice razmjene mladih *Inside Out* na Velebitu i Rabu (koja je održana uz podršku europskog programa *Mladi na djelu*), naši polaznici iz Hrvatske Majda, Viktor, Siniša i Dubravka su željeli pokazati što su sve naučili. Uz tehničku podršku *Outward Bounda* sami su 11.10.2012. organizirali jednodnevni program na Medvednici. Uz par savjeta iskusnih instruktora bacili su se na posao. Pozvali su mlade ljude s raznih strana Hrvatske. Odredili rute kretanja i osmislili zadatke. U ovom slučaju sretan broj polaznika bio je 13, a oni su podijeljeni u dvije grupe. Svi su dobili originalno osmišljene majice za ovu prigodu na temu *get out of the box*. Rute su bile začinjene zadacima. Neki zadaci su bile mozgalice, neki su zahtijevali veću količinu timskog rada, neki povjerenje u drugu osobu, a neki povjerenje u sebe. Dan je prepolovljen u planinarskom domu Puntijarka sa finim ručkom. Nakon toga su baterije za nastavak rješavanja zadataka bile napunjene. Dan je završio kod Tunela sa brojnim igrama i s osmijehom na licima. Program je uspio! Ponosni smo na naše mlade nade!

    Majda, jedna od organizatora, napravila je i (crtani) filmić:

    <iframe width="400" height="300" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/h2Ee9HmXy7M" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  EOS
  title_en: "Inside Out -- Sljeme",
  body_en: <<-EOS.strip_heredoc,
    After our international youth exchange hit *Inside Out* on Velebit and Rab (which was organized through the European program *Youth in Action*), our Croatian participants Majda, Viktor, Siniša and Dubravka wanted to show what they have learned to their friends. With the technical support of *Outward Bound Croatia*, on 10 November 2012 they organized a one-day program on Medvednica near Zagreb. They got a few tips from experienced Outward Bound instructors, and their project could start. They invited young people from different parts of Croatia. They selected routes for them on Medvednica and specified special tasks for them. This time the lucky number of participants was 13. After a short introduction they were divided into two groups. All were given originally designed T-shirts for this occasion with the message: *get out of the box*. The hike was spiced up with some tasks that participants had to solve along the way. For some of them they had to think a little bit more, some required more team work, in some of them they had to trust each other and in some they had to trust themselves. They had lunch in mountain hut Puntijarka. There the batteries for the rest of the hiking and tasks were charged. They spent the end of the day next to the Tunnel with many games and with a smile on everybody’s face. The program was a success! We are proud of our Croatian team from Velebit!

    Majda, one of the organizers, even made a (cartoon) video:

    <iframe width="400" height="300" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/h2Ee9HmXy7M" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  EOS
  album: @post1_album,
  created_at: "15/01/2013"
)
